\(\bullet\) \(H_0:Residuals\ are\ white\ noise\ \\ H_a:Residuals\ are\ not\ white\ noise\)

The formal test indicates that the residuals are autocorrelated. Since the p-value ( 0) is less than (0.05), we reject the null hypothesis. The dependent variable is not white noise.

\(\bullet\) \(H_0:Series\ are\ normally\ distributed\ vs\ H_a:Series\ are\ not\ normally\ distributed\)
The formal test indicates that residuals are not normally distributed. Since the p-value( 0) is less than (0.05) we reject the null hypothesis.
